8:T4c4a,<p>You’ll plan and <strong>assess risks</strong>, map the site, set boundaries and have an exit plan. Assign roles, use radios and hand signals, and keep a <strong><a href="https://cursedtours.com/5-essential-safety-tips-for-haunted-hospital-explorations/">safety</a> officer</strong>. Wear sturdy boots, layers, gloves and eye protection. Use red light, adjust low‑light camera settings, and test IR/thermal gear. Take baseline EMF readings and rule out interference. Secure a perimeter, <strong>document everything</strong> with timestamps, bag samples and preserve chain of custody — keep a skeptical, methodical mindset and you’ll learn practical next steps.</p>
<h2 id="key-takeaways">Key Takeaways</h2>
<ul>
